00:34:01,179 --> 00:34:05,600
inadvertently say something that should
be the title of their autobiography.

508
00:34:05,683 --> 00:34:08,603
Nick Fletcher, our gifted editor, and...

509
00:34:10,271 --> 00:34:13,691
...cinematic mastermind...

510
00:34:13,775 --> 00:34:18,112
One of the things you do in editing
is you'll hear a line,

511
00:34:18,196 --> 00:34:21,032
and go, "I don't like
the way the actor says that."

512
00:34:21,115 --> 00:34:24,953
Each time you make changes. You say
do this, do that. He has to sit there

513
00:34:25,036 --> 00:34:29,666
and assemble this whole thing. It's
just this mind-numbing jigsaw puzzle.

514
00:34:29,749 --> 00:34:34,379
Anyway, I come in after he's done all
this work. I go, "I don't like the way

515
00:34:34,462 --> 00:34:38,424
the guy says that line. Let me hear
the other takes, other versions of it.

516
00:34:38,508 --> 00:34:42,178
That's not a good read on that."
One of them that we had

517
00:34:42,262 --> 00:34:47,183
was of Freddy,
who was the head of the apiary.

518
00:34:47,267 --> 00:34:53,106
