01:09:13,166 --> 01:09:16,294
World's foremost bee expert,
but he missed the talking.

1045
01:09:16,377 --> 01:09:18,796
- That was Eric Idle.
- Played by Eric Idle.

1046
01:09:18,880 --> 01:09:24,802
In the end of that movie,
his plan was he wanted to be the first

1047
01:09:24,886 --> 01:09:30,266
bee king by transplanting
his head onto Barry's body

1048
01:09:30,350 --> 01:09:34,354
with some sort of machine he had
fashioned by watching The Fly

1049
01:09:34,437 --> 01:09:37,482
with Jeff Goldblum in 1986
over and over again.

1050
01:09:37,565 --> 01:09:42,737
He called it a Goldblum Machine. He
wanted to lure Barry into this chamber

1051
01:09:42,820 --> 01:09:46,866
and remove his head
and put the Willingham head

1052
01:09:46,950 --> 01:09:50,203
on Barry's head. Then he would
be the first king of the bees.

1053
01:09:50,286 --> 01:09:52,664
- And was so good.
- Steve Landesberg.

1054
01:09:52,747 --> 01:09:55,792
People are like,
"Why did you take him out? Why?"

1055
01:09:55,875 --> 01:09:59,545
Believe me, folks, we didn't want to,
but it's a tricky thing

1056
01:09:59,629 --> 01:10:02,507
when you're telling a story...
You can have...

1057
01:10:02,590 --> 01:10:06,970
I really fell prey to it...
you know, all the time.

1058
01:10:07,053 --> 01:10:11,182
Going off on detours and tangents
that had nothing to do with anything,

1059
01:10:11,266 --> 01:10:13,351
butjust things I thought were funny.

1060
01:10:13,434 --> 01:10:17,522
And when you play it for an audience,
we'd do test screenings,

1061
01:10:17,605 --> 01:10:21,526
the audience would get lost, confused.
They'd lose track of the film.

1062
01:10:21,609 --> 01:10:24,737
They end up not liking the movie
because they didn't know

1063
01:10:24,821 --> 01:10:27,782
- what the story was about.
- We had to stay with Barry.

1064
01:10:27,865 --> 01:10:31,327
The minute you deviated from that,
it never worked.

1065
01:10:31,411 --> 01:10:35,331
Once you didn't stay on his
point of view, they lost focus.

1066
01:10:35,415 --> 01:10:38,793
- Didn't know what to care about.
- It was frustrating for me

1067
01:10:38,876 --> 01:10:42,839
because I'm not interested in the story.
I'd rather just make jokes.

1068
01:10:42,922 --> 01:10:46,718
- We found that out.
- Tell them what really happened.

1069
01:10:46,801 --> 01:10:50,847
The biggest problem we had
in the story structure of the movie

1070
01:10:50,930 --> 01:10:53,808
was the end of the trial,
Barry wins the trial,

1071
01:10:53,892 --> 01:10:58,104
always kind of felt like the end
of the movie. It let the air out...

1072
01:10:58,187 --> 01:11:01,566
There was no more tension.
Problem solved, movie over.

1073
01:11:01,649 --> 01:11:06,696
We didn't want to do that traditional
structure where you end with the trial.

1074
01:11:06,779 --> 01:11:10,325
Somebody made the point to me
that it's very unusual

1075
01:11:10,408 --> 01:11:13,453
that the big trial scene
is in the middle of the movie.

1076
01:11:13,536 --> 01:11:16,331
- It's always at the end.
- Always.

1077
01:11:16,414 --> 01:11:20,460
- That's fresh then.
- So one of the ways we had to solve

1078
01:11:20,543 --> 01:11:25,089
the problem is the second he wins
the trial, Montgomery comes over

1079
01:11:25,173 --> 01:11:28,843
and warns him that this is gonna
have a bad consequence.

1080
01:11:28,927 --> 01:11:31,721
Here comes one of my favourite lines.

1081
01:11:34,349 --> 01:11:36,601
- "I'm an attorney!"
- I love that line.

1082
01:11:36,684 --> 01:11:38,311
We had a few different lines

1083
01:11:38,394 --> 01:11:42,315
that Barry would say
when he's on the bald guy's head,

1084
01:11:42,398 --> 01:11:45,235
so the guy doesn't attack him.
Trying to explain,

1085
01:11:45,318 --> 01:11:49,197
"I'm notjust a bee.
I'm talking, I'm on your side."

1086
01:11:49,280 --> 01:11:55,411
So one of them was "I'm an attorney".
One was "I'm a frequent flier member".

1087
01:11:55,495 --> 01:11:58,915
- Miles plus.
- The guy said, "Who isn't?"

1088
01:11:58,998 --> 01:12:04,087
